# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: RazaphelQuestionsWarrior
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah looked at the spirit intently."
    new "Sarah looked at the spirit intently."

    old "You spoke of the Gods, the Pantheon. If they are as real as you claim, where are they then?"
    new "You spoke of the Gods, the Pantheon. If they are as real as you claim, where are they then?"

    old "When the war between your world and my own began, it was the Gods from my world, the Three Sisters, who dealt the first blow."
    new "When the war between your world and my own began, it was the Gods from my world, the Three Sisters, who dealt the first blow."

    old "Striking at the heart of one of your Gods, they did what had been until then unconceivable."
    new "Striking at the heart of one of your Gods, they did what had been until then unconceivable."

    old "They killed him."
    new "They killed him."

    old "As your Pantheon saw the impossible and witnessed their brother falling to the earth, they felt for the first time fear."
    new "As your Pantheon saw the impossible and witnessed their brother falling to the earth, they felt for the first time fear."

    old "They fled beyond the borders of this world, hiding themselves in a space that even they themselves are blind to."
    new "They fled beyond the borders of this world, hiding themselves in a space that even they themselves are blind to."

    old "Tell me then, what happened to your race after the war?"
    new "Tell me then, what happened to your race after the war?"

    old "When we were defeated, we were thrown back into our own world. But our world remained trapped beneath yours."
    new "When we were defeated, we were thrown back into our own world. But our world remained trapped beneath yours."

    old "Each passing moment, the space of your world exterts itself against ours, and presses ours further up against the edges of existence."
    new "Each passing moment, the space of your world exterts itself against ours, and presses ours further up against the edges of existence."

    old "I don't understand what that means."
    new "I don't understand what that means."

    old "Imagine yourself, trapped between two panes of glass, unbreakable."
    new "Imagine yourself, trapped between two panes of glass, unbreakable."

    old "Every passing moment, the glass on each side of you is wound tighter and tighter."
    new "Every passing moment, the glass on each side of you is wound tighter and tighter."

    old "Each moment, it presses down on your body."
    new "Each moment, it presses down on your body."

    old "Undying, you are trapped. You can neither move nor escape. And every moment, for all of eternity, the press is wound tighter still."
    new "Undying, you are trapped. You can neither move nor escape. And every moment, for all of eternity, the press is wound tighter still."

    old "Every bone in your body breaks, every fragment of your body extends."
    new "Every bone in your body breaks, every fragment of your body extends."

    old "Such has been the fate of my race for millenia now."
    new "Such has been the fate of my race for millenia now."

    old "You said that the Empress reached out to your world. Why?"
    new "You said that the Empress reached out to your world. Why?"

    old "She sought immortality."
    new "She sought immortality."

    old "In your world, such a thing is rare, but in my world it is common."
    new "In your world, such a thing is rare, but in my world it is common."

    old "The Gods of my world, the Three Sisters, granted each living creature with an everlasting life."
    new "The Gods of my world, the Three Sisters, granted each living creature with an everlasting life."

    old "They desired only that we made use of it for as long as we pleased, and when we were finished with life, we could go to the tower of dying, and fade away."
    new "They desired only that we made use of it for as long as we pleased, and when we were finished with life, we could go to the tower of dying, and fade away."

    old "Our world was a paradise."
    new "Our world was a paradise."

    old "Hunger. Famine. War. Such things that are common in your world were strangers to mine."
    new "Hunger. Famine. War. Such things that are common in your world were strangers to mine."

    old "Before the great suffering began, my race had never known discomfort of any kind."
    new "Before the great suffering began, my race had never known discomfort of any kind."

    old "Sarah considered her question for a while."
    new "Sarah considered her question for a while."

    old "The Gods...they are all knowing and all powerful. How could they not have prevented this?"
    new "The Gods...they are all knowing and all powerful. How could they not have prevented this?"

    old "The Gods are inherent to the nature of the world itself."
    new "The Gods are inherent to the nature of the world itself."

    old "They are the well from which all the laws that govern nature spring forth."
    new "They are the well from which all the laws that govern nature spring forth."

    old "It is this fact that makes them know the world and all its elements, for they are imbued within it."
    new "It is this fact that makes them know the world and all its elements, for they are imbued within it."

    old "But they are only inherent to the nature of their own world."
    new "But they are only inherent to the nature of their own world."

    old "The Gods had no knowledge of the world beyond their own. From their point of view, the ritual would never succeed."
    new "The Gods had no knowledge of the world beyond their own. From their point of view, the ritual would never succeed."

    old "The Gods believed this because they could not perceive my world."
    new "The Gods believed this because they could not perceive my world."

    old "Meanwhile, in my world, my Gods were equally blind to yours, and could not conceive of what was soon to happen."
    new "Meanwhile, in my world, my Gods were equally blind to yours, and could not conceive of what was soon to happen."

    old "But could they not have considered that it would happen? How were they so sure the ritual would fail?"
    new "But could they not have considered that it would happen? How were they so sure the ritual would fail?"

    old "They were sure in the way the Gods are always sure."
    new "They were sure in the way the Gods are always sure."

    old "How do you explain to a creature that knows everything, that they do not know something?"
    new "How do you explain to a creature that knows everything, that they do not know something?"

    old "To the Gods, the idea of not knowing something, has been itself inconceivable, for since creation they have known everything."
    new "To the Gods, the idea of not knowing something, has been itself inconceivable, for since creation they have known everything."

    old "For them, this was the first time since the dawn of this world that they have ever been wrong about anything."
    new "For them, this was the first time since the dawn of this world that they have ever been wrong about anything."

    old "As such, the idea that they might be wrong, was an inconceivable notion to them."
    new "As such, the idea that they might be wrong, was an inconceivable notion to them."

    old "A thought they could literally not think."
    new "A thought they could literally not think."

    old "I have asked all that I need to know"
    new "I have asked all that I need to know"

    old "Sarah looked up at the spirit."
    new "Sarah looked up at the spirit."

    old "I've asked you everything that I need to know."
    new "I've asked you everything that I need to know."

    old "For a moment, she saw the spirit twist and move."
    new "For a moment, she saw the spirit twist and move."

    old "You have asked me all you wish to know, but one question still remains to you."
    new "You have asked me all you wish to know, but one question still remains to you."

    old "Sarah considered, but knew the question that still lingered."
    new "Sarah considered, but knew the question that still lingered."

    old "I have not yet asked you what this has to do with me. Why I should concern myself with ancient history."
    new "I have not yet asked you what this has to do with me. Why I should concern myself with ancient history."

    old "Or why you have brought me here."
    new "Or why you have brought me here."

    old "I shall keep my word to you and speak only truth."
    new "I shall keep my word to you and speak only truth."

    old "The spirit's voice was soft and melodic."
    new "The spirit's voice was soft and melodic."

    old "When the Gods of your world fled, wounded and fearful, there was no place where they might seek refuge."
    new "When the Gods of your world fled, wounded and fearful, there was no place where they might seek refuge."

    old "No place where the Three Sisters would not know to find them."
    new "No place where the Three Sisters would not know to find them."

    old "So in turn, the Gods of your world blinded themselves even to themselves."
    new "So in turn, the Gods of your world blinded themselves even to themselves."

    old "They hid away in a void beyond where anyone could reach them. A place from which they themselves did not even know to return."
    new "They hid away in a void beyond where anyone could reach them. A place from which they themselves did not even know to return."

    old "And even now, they wander there, blinded to the world."
    new "And even now, they wander there, blinded to the world."

    old "Sarah tried to conceive of it, wandering an eternal darkness, no way home. It was not entirely unfamiliar to her."
    new "Sarah tried to conceive of it, wandering an eternal darkness, no way home. It was not entirely unfamiliar to her."

    old "Before they ran, they created their ultimate weapon."
    new "Before they ran, they created their ultimate weapon."

    old "The Golden Path."
    new "The Golden Path."

    old "Hidden away, they could not affect the world. Instead, they drafted the very story of their own return."
    new "Hidden away, they could not affect the world. Instead, they drafted the very story of their own return."

    old "Gathered in their sacred halls, your Pantheon gathered up all their might and foresaw all the possible movements of the world."
    new "Gathered in their sacred halls, your Pantheon gathered up all their might and foresaw all the possible movements of the world."

    old "From every mountain, down to every blade of grass, and ensnaring every living soul, they authored the Golden Path."
    new "From every mountain, down to every blade of grass, and ensnaring every living soul, they authored the Golden Path."

    old "Ever since their departure, all of this world's history has been little more than a play."
    new "Ever since their departure, all of this world's history has been little more than a play."

    old "Each thing playing its part, each soul living out its life in accordance to the design."
    new "Each thing playing its part, each soul living out its life in accordance to the design."

    old "Kingdoms rising and falling, all by careful design."
    new "Kingdoms rising and falling, all by careful design."

    old "A design in which every path bends towards the same desination."
    new "A design in which every path bends towards the same desination."

    old "The spirit paused."
    new "The spirit paused."

    old "Emanation."
    new "Emanation."

    old "Sarah stared at the spirit. Something about what it had said resonated with her, though she struggled to define what."
    new "Sarah stared at the spirit. Something about what it had said resonated with her, though she struggled to define what."

    old "Emanation?"
    new "Emanation?"

    old "Yes, their great return."
    new "Yes, their great return."

    old "When the beacon that will guide them back to this world is lit. When they will sweep back and resume their dominion over the world."
    new "When the beacon that will guide them back to this world is lit. When they will sweep back and resume their dominion over the world."

    old "Sarah found it hard to believe the spirit, but harder still to disbelieve him."
    new "Sarah found it hard to believe the spirit, but harder still to disbelieve him."

    old "So all of history...every creature, every human...has been like a puppet? That can't be so."
    new "So all of history...every creature, every human...has been like a puppet? That can't be so."

    old "I am in control of my own life, I make my own decisions. I know that much."
    new "I am in control of my own life, I make my own decisions. I know that much."

    old "The spirit twisted."
    new "The spirit twisted."

    old "This is the subtlety of their craft, to make their thoughts come to you as your own."
    new "This is the subtlety of their craft, to make their thoughts come to you as your own."

    old "But you are true that it is not so crude that only one path unfolds itself."
    new "But you are true that it is not so crude that only one path unfolds itself."

    old "Even the Gods of your world cannot control so accurately every atom. Not while they are hidden, at least."
    new "Even the Gods of your world cannot control so accurately every atom. Not while they are hidden, at least."

    old "Their plan is like a bridge, on which they stand on each side."
    new "Their plan is like a bridge, on which they stand on each side."

    old "You can cross the bridge in any way you wish or feel, but it will change nothing."
    new "You can cross the bridge in any way you wish or feel, but it will change nothing."

    old "They dominate the beginning and the end."
    new "They dominate the beginning and the end."

    old "And people are just mindless creatures, used by them?"
    new "And people are just mindless creatures, used by them?"

    old "Some, but not all."
    new "Some, but not all."

    old "Not all souls have been crafted equally by them."
    new "Not all souls have been crafted equally by them."

    old "Those most essential to their designs are souls of a greater size, and the greater soul dominates the lesser soul."
    new "Those most essential to their designs are souls of a greater size, and the greater soul dominates the lesser soul."

    old "Those gifted with such divine purpose, find the world often bending to their own will. Their own purpose."
    new "Those gifted with such divine purpose, find the world often bending to their own will. Their own purpose."

    old "Over centuries...millenia...I have worked to unravel their schemes and their plans."
    new "Over centuries...millenia...I have worked to unravel their schemes and their plans."

    old "As a creature from the other world, their sight over me was limited."
    new "As a creature from the other world, their sight over me was limited."

    old "From beneath this world, I could see the cycles of the world unfold, how again and again my race was broken as your Gods returned."
    new "From beneath this world, I could see the cycles of the world unfold, how again and again my race was broken as your Gods returned."

    old "Again and again, I watched them burn in divine flame, undying yet forever lost."
    new "Again and again, I watched them burn in divine flame, undying yet forever lost."

    old "And though each cycle carried with it the same conclusion, I witnessed many different faces who brought about our ruin."
    new "And though each cycle carried with it the same conclusion, I witnessed many different faces who brought about our ruin."

    old "Seven."
    new "Seven."

    old "Seven?"
    new "Seven?"

    old "Yes. There are by my estimation only seven people, whose souls were made so uniquely that they would bring about the ultimate victory for the Gods."
    new "Yes. There are by my estimation only seven people, whose souls were made so uniquely that they would bring about the ultimate victory for the Gods."

    old "Seven people who lit the beacon and filled up the world with blinding light."
    new "Seven people who lit the beacon and filled up the world with blinding light."

    old "You are one of them, I have seen it in my dreams."
    new "You are one of them, I have seen it in my dreams."

    old "Sarah walked nearer to the monolith, instinctively."
    new "Sarah walked nearer to the monolith, instinctively."

    old "You have seen me...in your dreams?"
    new "You have seen me...in your dreams?"

    old "Yes. Full of fire, your soul so bright it poured out of you like light from stars, your hair blazing flame."
    new "Yes. Full of fire, your soul so bright it poured out of you like light from stars, your hair blazing flame."

    old "And my race, broken and defeated, cast into the eternal pit. This time, without escape."
    new "And my race, broken and defeated, cast into the eternal pit. This time, without escape."

    old "Sarah tried to imagine what he told her. It seemed so impossible, and yet a part of her knew the spirit kept to it's word, it spoke truth."
    new "Sarah tried to imagine what he told her. It seemed so impossible, and yet a part of her knew the spirit kept to it's word, it spoke truth."

    old "So...that is my destiny?"
    new "So...that is my destiny?"

    old "It need not be."
    new "It need not be."

    old "I can break the bond that binds you to their design."
    new "I can break the bond that binds you to their design."

    old "I can shatter the link between yourself and the divine."
    new "I can shatter the link between yourself and the divine."

    old "Why would I want that?"
    new "Why would I want that?"

    old "Because ever since you left your homeland, you have yearned to be free."
    new "Because ever since you left your homeland, you have yearned to be free."

    old "Free from fear. Free from threats of violence. Free to control your own fate."
    new "Free from fear. Free from threats of violence. Free to control your own fate."

    old "Does it not enrage you that you are but a puppet in their designs?"
    new "Does it not enrage you that you are but a puppet in their designs?"

    old "The world spun around her as she tried to make sense of it all."
    new "The world spun around her as she tried to make sense of it all."

    old "All her life, decided for her by some Pantheon. Even if her fate was good, it would not be hers. Not truly."
    new "All her life, decided for her by some Pantheon. Even if her fate was good, it would not be hers. Not truly."

    old "You will never truly be free, for as long as you walk in their design."
    new "You will never truly be free, for as long as you walk in their design."

    old "What then? What option do I have?"
    new "What then? What option do I have?"

    old "When the barriers between the world were put up and my race was thrown underneath, I managed to escape."
    new "When the barriers between the world were put up and my race was thrown underneath, I managed to escape."

    old "I carried with me this monolith, a fragment of a relic from my world."
    new "I carried with me this monolith, a fragment of a relic from my world."

    old "The fate stones are small fragments, but this monolith does in full what they only do in part."
    new "The fate stones are small fragments, but this monolith does in full what they only do in part."

    old "It makes the Gods blind to the the space around it."
    new "It makes the Gods blind to the the space around it."

    old "Sarah looked up and down the ancient monolith. Untouched by any signs of decay. Humming with unseen power."
    new "Sarah looked up and down the ancient monolith. Untouched by any signs of decay. Humming with unseen power."

    old "Lay your hand upon its surface and I will infuse its essence with your own."
    new "Lay your hand upon its surface and I will infuse its essence with your own."

    old "You will be a creature of two worlds. Possessing the same golden soul, but lost to the sight of the Gods."
    new "You will be a creature of two worlds. Possessing the same golden soul, but lost to the sight of the Gods."

    old "Invisible to them, you can move again their designs."
    new "Invisible to them, you can move again their designs."

    old "You can move, truly free."
    new "You can move, truly free."

    old "Touch the stone and she would be free. Sarah considered it."
    new "Touch the stone and she would be free. Sarah considered it."

    old "But who was this spirit, truly? She sensed there was a truth in his words, but truth did not meant that he could not deceive."
    new "But who was this spirit, truly? She sensed there was a truth in his words, but truth did not meant that he could not deceive."

    old "Perhaps the spirit had only told her enough truth to twist her to it's own designs."
    new "Perhaps the spirit had only told her enough truth to twist her to it's own designs."

    old "What did she truly know of such witchcraft?"
    new "What did she truly know of such witchcraft?"

    old "And yet, if he spoke true and she walked away...would she be forever a slave?"
    new "And yet, if he spoke true and she walked away...would she be forever a slave?"

    old "Bound to some design that had been imposed upon her before she'd even been born? Was all her life to be a fool's performance?"
    new "Bound to some design that had been imposed upon her before she'd even been born? Was all her life to be a fool's performance?"

    old "Place your hands upon the monolith"
    new "Place your hands upon the monolith"

    old "Sarah steps forward, climbing the steps towards the monolith."
    new "Sarah steps forward, climbing the steps towards the monolith."

    old "As she nears it, she can feel it humming, the vibrations running through her armor. Through her body."
    new "As she nears it, she can feel it humming, the vibrations running through her armor. Through her body."

    old "What will happen if I do this?"
    new "What will happen if I do this?"

    old "You will be free."
    new "You will be free."

    old "But will I still be myself?"
    new "But will I still be myself?"

    old "For a moment, the spirit was silent."
    new "For a moment, the spirit was silent."

    old "For the first time in your life, Sarah, you will truly be yourself."
    new "For the first time in your life, Sarah, you will truly be yourself."

    old "Never again will you be bound to the whims of another."
    new "Never again will you be bound to the whims of another."

    old "For a moment, she hesitated longer."
    new "For a moment, she hesitated longer."

    old "Then, Sarah reached out and placed one hand upon the monolith."
    new "Then, Sarah reached out and placed one hand upon the monolith."

    old "The surface of it felt smooth. It was cold in a subtle, persistent way, reaching through even her mailed gloves."
    new "The surface of it felt smooth. It was cold in a subtle, persistent way, reaching through even her mailed gloves."

    old "As the cold clung to her hand and climbed up further along her body, Sarah felt herself shiver."
    new "As the cold clung to her hand and climbed up further along her body, Sarah felt herself shiver."

    old "And yet she knew she both would not and could not remove her hand."
    new "And yet she knew she both would not and could not remove her hand."

    old "Crawling, inch by inch, the cold dug its way up through her arm."
    new "Crawling, inch by inch, the cold dug its way up through her arm."

    old "As it ran further it ran deeper as well, until all of her arm felt as though it was frozen."
    new "As it ran further it ran deeper as well, until all of her arm felt as though it was frozen."

    old "A roaring pain rose up and faded into a discomforting numbness."
    new "A roaring pain rose up and faded into a discomforting numbness."

    old "Sarah drew in a breath, short and haggard."
    new "Sarah drew in a breath, short and haggard."

    old "Keep breathing, she told herself, even as the cold advanced."
    new "Keep breathing, she told herself, even as the cold advanced."

    old "Up from her arm, into her chest and out into every limb."
    new "Up from her arm, into her chest and out into every limb."

    old "Spreading, deeper, rooting into her."
    new "Spreading, deeper, rooting into her."

    old "Her organs shuttered. Her breath turned to frost. Her skin turned blue."
    new "Her organs shuttered. Her breath turned to frost. Her skin turned blue."

    old "And yet her hand remained fixed."
    new "And yet her hand remained fixed."

    old "All around her, she could see the spirit advance, it's misty shape twisting around her body."
    new "All around her, she could see the spirit advance, it's misty shape twisting around her body."

    old "Passing in and over her."
    new "Passing in and over her."

    old "And for a brief moment, the blizzard peaked and her life ended."
    new "And for a brief moment, the blizzard peaked and her life ended."

    old "Five beats of a her heart, she counted missing."
    new "Five beats of a her heart, she counted missing."

    old "Then, from the core of herself, a faint spark of heat, like a first sign of spring."
    new "Then, from the core of herself, a faint spark of heat, like a first sign of spring."

    old "The spark grew and grew, driving out and forcing away the heat."
    new "The spark grew and grew, driving out and forcing away the heat."

    old "Slowly, her organs resumed, and all other hints of the cold were slowly driven out."
    new "Slowly, her organs resumed, and all other hints of the cold were slowly driven out."

    old "In the end, she leaned up against the monolith, her palm still planted there."
    new "In the end, she leaned up against the monolith, her palm still planted there."

    old "Sarah breathed heavily as she tried to recover."
    new "Sarah breathed heavily as she tried to recover."

    old "As she looked up, she realized the spirit was gone."
    new "As she looked up, she realized the spirit was gone."

    old "R-R-Razaphel."
    new "R-R-Razaphel."

    old "Sarah stuttered the words, still somewhat shivering from the remnants of the cold."
    new "Sarah stuttered the words, still somewhat shivering from the remnants of the cold."

    old "I am here."
    new "I am here."

    old "Where?"
    new "Where?"

    old "Where you are."
    new "Where you are."

    old "Sarah watched as she spirit emerged from her own body, turning its face mask towards her."
    new "Sarah watched as she spirit emerged from her own body, turning its face mask towards her."

    old "You're...a part of me?"
    new "You're...a part of me?"

    old "Not quite."
    new "Not quite."

    old "I can move in the wake of your body, like waves to a ship."
    new "I can move in the wake of your body, like waves to a ship."

    old "The essential parts of the monolith are imbued in you, and I can travel with it."
    new "The essential parts of the monolith are imbued in you, and I can travel with it."

    old "And what if I don't want that?"
    new "And what if I don't want that?"

    old "Only will it."
    new "Only will it."

    old "Sarah willed the spirit the fade, and an in instant, the spirit was gone."
    new "Sarah willed the spirit the fade, and an in instant, the spirit was gone."

    old "With the same ease, she summoned the spirit back."
    new "With the same ease, she summoned the spirit back."

    old "As you see, there is only one master here."
    new "As you see, there is only one master here."

    old "Sarah rolled her shoulders, driving out the last reminders of the cold."
    new "Sarah rolled her shoulders, driving out the last reminders of the cold."

    old "She had expected a ritual with more violence."
    new "She had expected a ritual with more violence."

    old "Sarah searched her body. Her mind. Her soul. She searched everywhere for a sign that she was somehow changed. Different."
    new "Sarah searched her body. Her mind. Her soul. She searched everywhere for a sign that she was somehow changed. Different."

    old "Nothing seemed to suggest it."
    new "Nothing seemed to suggest it."

    old "I feel...the same."
    new "I feel...the same."

    old "You have changed, as clear from night to day, but to you it will feel no different."
    new "You have changed, as clear from night to day, but to you it will feel no different."

    old "But the world will arc and bend in ways we cannot yet imagine. The world has been upended, Sarah."
    new "But the world will arc and bend in ways we cannot yet imagine. The world has been upended, Sarah."

    old "She imagined she detected a hint of gladness in the spirit's voice."
    new "She imagined she detected a hint of gladness in the spirit's voice."

    old "Tell me, how do I get out of this place?"
    new "Tell me, how do I get out of this place?"

    old "They will save you in a moment."
    new "They will save you in a moment."

    old "Save me?"
    new "Save me?"

    old "Sarah felt the world fade into darkness."
    new "Sarah felt the world fade into darkness."

    old "Reject Razaphel's offer"
    new "Reject Razaphel's offer"

    old "I won't do it."
    new "I won't do it."

    old "For a moment, the spirit lingered."
    new "For a moment, the spirit lingered."

    old "In my dream I have been here before. In my dreams I have heard you tell me yes. Tell me no."
    new "In my dream I have been here before. In my dreams I have heard you tell me yes. Tell me no."

    old "To hear you say the words now, to hear you condemn my race to torment."
    new "To hear you say the words now, to hear you condemn my race to torment."

    old "Sarah looked at the spirit."
    new "Sarah looked at the spirit."

    old "You say that I have condemned your race to a fate worse than death. Will you not fight me?"
    new "You say that I have condemned your race to a fate worse than death. Will you not fight me?"

    old "Fight you?"
    new "Fight you?"

    old "Dear Sarah, old friend, I have never hated you. Even in the dreams where you held the sword that condemned us."
    new "Dear Sarah, old friend, I have never hated you. Even in the dreams where you held the sword that condemned us."

    old "I never hated you because it was never you who did it. Nor any of the others."
    new "I never hated you because it was never you who did it. Nor any of the others."

    old "Each of you is bound and twisted up in a design beyond your ability to see. Beyond your ability to escape."
    new "Each of you is bound and twisted up in a design beyond your ability to see. Beyond your ability to escape."

    old "I was a fool for trying."
    new "I was a fool for trying."

    old "There is no point in fighting you. The stones are set in place. Fate is written."
